Kazakhmys Plc (KAZ) ,  Kazakhstan â€™s biggest
copper producer, resumed mining at Konyrat, where work stopped
in 2008, targeting the extraction of 3.5 million metric tons of
copper ore this year.  The company plans to excavate about 57 million tons of
copper ore at Konyrat in the next nine years before closing the
mine, Kazakhmys said in a statement posted on the Kazakhstan
